{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"solar-doughty-megaraptor","description":"## Why\nMake the long-running service observable and make every failure LOUD and troubleshootable — hangs, errors, and stuck states must be highly visible, per the operability requirement. Also serve the remote liveness/queue surface `land` reads. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/autolander/loop.py` — EDIT: the read-only HTTP status endpoint + the `AUTOLANDER_ERROR` marker emission + the time-to-land metric emit.\n- `infra/scripts/observability.sh` — EDIT: the `autolander_errors` + `autolander_time_to_land_seconds` `PutMetricData` feeders.\n- `infra/terraform/monitoring_autolander.tf` — NEW: the alarms.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **Read-only status endpoint (prior art: Zuul `zuul-web`, Tide `deck`):** a small read-only HTTP endpoint on the bot serving JSON — the current `wipChain` (change, `phase`, `tested_shas`, **time-in-phase**), the count of `Autosubmit`-set-and-waiting changes, and **`heartbeat_age_s`** (integer seconds since the last heartbeat write — the exact field `land`'s `lander_down` binds to). Read-only, non-secret; bound so agents can reach it.\n- [ ] **Error metric (LOUD by default):** `observability.sh` publishes `rebar/host:autolander_errors` (`PutMetricData`) from THREE feeders — the `AUTOLANDER_ERROR` structured stdout marker (the loop writes it on **any** unhandled error, then hands the current stack back rather than wedging silently), the container `unhealthy` Docker health-state (via `docker inspect --format '{{.State.Health.Status}}'`, NOT a journald grep), and each `lander_down`/handback event — with an alarm in `monitoring_autolander.tf`.\n- [ ] **Stuck-state alarm (high visibility):** a **time-in-phase alarm** fires when a `wipChain` sits in any non-`idle` phase past a threshold (a wedged-but-alive bot), so a hang that autoheal does not catch is still visible for troubleshooting.\n- [ ] **Time-to-land metric:** emit `autolander_time_to_land_seconds` (explicit metric name) as **individual `Value` datapoints** per landed change (NOT `StatisticValues` — CloudWatch computes extended-statistic percentiles only from raw `Value` datapoints); p50/p90/p99 come from CloudWatch extended statistics downstream (no hard-coded buckets). **In-session proof = the datapoint is published** for one landed change; populated percentiles are an expected post-deploy outcome, not an in-sprint deliverable.\n- [ ] The service logs to container stdout and NEVER writes `session_log`.\n- [ ] **Tests:** the status endpoint returns the documented JSON shape (incl. `heartbeat_age_s`); a forced error produces an `AUTOLANDER_ERROR` marker + a metric datapoint; the time-in-phase alarm expression is unit-checked.","id":"9a6f-065d-91c4-4e03","parent_id":"3c55-2af3-0c9c-4b11","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"S5c Observability (loud errors + stuck-state alarm) + read-only status endpoint"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783825273281580001,"uuid":"d3761d90-6697-4096-9bfc-81907e3ce215"}